<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1927,2034]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1927,1953]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pandeid hydroids with colonies ectoparasitic on fishes and on ichthyoparasitic copepods. Zooids monomorphic or dimorphic, atentaculate, clavate to tubular, arising from a basal encrusting plate or reticular hydrorhiza; perisarc absent.
</paragraph>
